Privacy Policy for Fitness & Workout
Last Modified: September 2024
I. INTRODUCTION
Logic Fusion, LLC (“we,” “us,” or “our”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal information when you use the Fitness & Workout mobile application (the “App”).
When we mention personal data, we mean information that can identify you either directly or indirectly, such as your name, email, or unique identifiers. This Privacy Policy applies to all users of the App. By using the App, you agree to the terms of this policy.
II. DATA COLLECTION
We collect different types of information:
1.
Personal Information You Provide:
•
When you register using “Sign in with Apple” or another method, we may collect your email address (or an anonymous email via Apple’s “Hide My Email” feature).
•
Additional information like name, age, and fitness data may be collected to provide personalized recommendations and insights.
2.
Automatically Collected Information:
•
We may collect information about your device, such as its operating system, IP address, and location data.
•
App usage details, such as session duration, interactions, and error reports, may also be logged.
3.
Payment Data:
•
We do not store credit card information directly. However, payment transactions are processed through secure third-party services.
III. USE OF PERSONAL DATA
We use your information for various purposes, including:
•
Providing Services: To deliver the functionalities of the App, such as personalized workout plans or progress tracking.
•
Improving the App: To analyze user activity and enhance the user experience.
•
Marketing: With your consent, we may send newsletters and promotional offers via email. If you choose “Sign in with Apple” and select to hide your email, we will receive a unique, random email address generated by Apple that forwards communications to you.
You may opt out of receiving newsletters at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link in our emails.
IV. DATA SHARING
We do not sell or rent your personal data to third parties. However, we may share your data with:
•
Service Providers: We work with third-party providers to help us operate the App, including analytics services and email marketing tools. These third parties are bound by privacy obligations.
•
Legal Obligations: We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to a legal request, such as a subpoena or court order.
•
Business Transfers: In the event of a merger or sale, your information may be transferred as part of the transaction.
V. SECURITY AND RETENTION
We prioritize the security of your personal data. We employ various technical and organizational measures to prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, or misuse of your data.
Personal data is retained as long as necessary to provide the App’s services or comply with legal obligations. If you request deletion of your data, we will honor your request within a reasonable timeframe.
VI. USER RIGHTS
Massachusetts residents have the right to:
•
Access: Request access to the personal data we have collected about you.
•
Rectification: Ask us to correct any inaccurate or incomplete data.
•
Deletion: Request the deletion of your personal data.
•
Opt-out of marketing: Choose not to receive promotional communications from us.
You can exercise these rights by contacting us through the support form in the App.
VII. INTERNATIONAL TRANSFERS
As a company operating globally, your personal information may be transferred to other countries, including the U.S. These countries may have data protection laws that differ from those in your jurisdiction. By using the App, you consent to such transfers.
VIII. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be communicated through the App, and your continued use of the App after such changes will signify your acceptance of the new terms.